  • Method Details

    • conditionalSelect

      public static <R> R conditionalSelect(boolean condition, Supplier<R> supplierIfTrue, Supplier<R> supplierIfFalse)
      Selects and returns a value from one of two suppliers based on a boolean condition.

      This method is the equivalent of the ternary operator (condition ? valueIfTrue : valueIfFalse) but uses Suppliers to ensure **lazy evaluation**. Only the Supplier corresponding to the current state of the condition will have its get() method called, avoiding potentially costly operations if their result is not needed.

      Type Parameters:
      R - The common return type of both suppliers and the method.
      Parameters:
      condition - The boolean expression to evaluate.
      supplierIfTrue - The supplier whose get() method is called and returned if the condition is true.
      supplierIfFalse - The supplier whose get() method is called and returned if the condition is false.
      Returns:
      The value provided by the selected supplier.
      Since:
      2.2.0

    • allMatchLazy

      public static boolean allMatchLazy(BooleanSupplier... suppliers)
      Performs a lazy logical AND (AllMatch) operation across the provided boolean expressions.

      It returns true only if all boolean expressions supplied return true. This method guarantees **short-circuit evaluation**: it stops and returns false immediately upon finding the first supplier that returns false.

      Parameters:
      suppliers - The BooleanSuppliers containing the boolean expressions to evaluate.
      Returns:
      true if all suppliers return true, false otherwise.

    • anyMatchLazy

      public static boolean anyMatchLazy(BooleanSupplier... suppliers)
      Performs a lazy logical OR (AnyMatch) operation across the provided boolean expressions.

      It returns true if at least one boolean expression supplied returns true. This method guarantees **short-circuit evaluation**: it stops and returns true immediately upon finding the first supplier that returns true.

      Parameters:
      suppliers - The BooleanSuppliers containing the boolean expressions to evaluate.
      Returns:
      true if at least one supplier returns true, false otherwise.
